VALUES ('54a55116-c82f-4105-bad1-3f159201009c', 'Which choice best describes the overall structure of the text?', 'Within cognitive neuroscience, the migration of a metaphor across disciplines has long been read as straightforward progress, a reading that the early proponents—whose archives, only recently catalogued, complicate the received chronology—did much to entrench. What that account treats as predictive coding, however, the tabulated divergence reframes: the apparent advance, far from being intrinsic, was conditioned by an institutional metaplasticity that the standard narrative cannot model. Granting that the correlation is genuine, one must still resist the inference that it is causal, for the same configuration recurs though never once the governing parameter is relaxed.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"The text opens by foregrounding a conventional reading of its subject. It then concedes part of a critique only to show that the critic''s own alternative reproduces the flaw, undermining the critique on structural grounds —against the impression the opening invites.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: its second sentence is the only one that satisfies the discriminating condition."},{"id":"B","text":"The text opens by foregrounding a conventional reading of its subject. It then endorses the critique outright, stopping at the concession without complicating it further —against the impression the opening invites, as the argument is staged.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Rhetorical Misclassification] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"C","text":"The text opens by foregrounding a conventional reading of its subject. It then identifies the structural reversal but misattributes it to the original theory rather than to the critic''s alternative —against the impression the opening invites.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Rhetorical Misclassification] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"D","text":"The text opens by foregrounding a conventional reading of its subject. It then proposes a wholly new alternative, treating the prior positions as superseded —against the impression the opening invites, on the evidence presented.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Over-Extrapolation] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Logical Reconstruction:
